cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of functional languages with parallel patterns for generating hardware, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of high-level abstractions for hardware design, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper presents optimizations for improving the performance of hardware generated from parallel patterns, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of programming FPGAs, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
